Enum MatcherFamily

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<MatcherFamily>
      • bio.singa.structure.model.families.MatcherFamily
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    StructuralFamily<MatcherFamily>, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<MatcherFamily>
    public enum MatcherFamily
extends java.lang.Enum<MatcherFamily>
implements StructuralFamily<MatcherFamily>
    This is a StructuralFamily that groups others. Using this, one can employ the definition of exchanges to be allowed for a group of residues.

        public static final java.util.EnumSet<MatcherFamily> GUTTERIDGE
        The following types are grouped according to 
              Gutteridge, A. and Thornton, J. M.:
      Understanding nature's catalytic toolkit Trends in biochemical sciences, Elsevier, 2005, 30, 622-629.

      • FUNCTIONAL

        public static java.util.EnumSet<MatcherFamily> FUNCTIONAL
        The following types are grouped according to functional chemical groups: 
              aromatic (a)             F,Y,W
      negatively charged (n)   D,E
      positively charged (p)   K,R,H
      polar, uncharged (o)     P,N,Q,C,T,S
      nonpolar, aliphatic (i)  G,A,V,L,M,I

      • PHYSICOCHEMICAL

        public static java.util.EnumSet<MatcherFamily> PHYSICOCHEMICAL
        The following types are grouped according to the definition of Livingstone and Barton 1993. 
              aromatic (a)             Y,W,F
      negatively charged (n)   D,E
      positively charged (p)   K,R,H
      polar, uncharged (u)     Q,M,C,P,N,T
      tiny (t)                 A,G,S
      aliphatic (p)            L,I,V
